replies.body:
Words are not good nor evil. Words are what we as individuals intend them to mean. Good words can mean bad things and bad words can mean good things. There is no universal truth as to what any given word means. You CAN just take pre-existing words and change them as you see fit. They're words. God didn't give us those words. Those words are pulled out of our asses and given meaning that was also pulled from our asses. 

Unless of course you think that a 2-year old who just mimicks a word that they hear is evil and racist.

{{sticker:darius-angry}}
